.ident	"@(#)niccfg:help/rx_buf_num	1.1"
.related /dev/null
.title Receive Buffer Help Screen
 You must now specify the number of receive buffers that the 
 driver should pre-allocate.  To display the list of choices, 
 press <F2>. 

 If you are unsure of this value, you should shut down your 
 system now and follow the manufacturer's instructions on how 
 to configure your card for this setting. 

 EXITING HELP 
 Press <Esc> to return to the Network Interface Card 
 Configuration Screen. 
